The paper discusses resampling methods for particle filtering, which is a common technique used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also introduces a new resampling scheme and compares it to existing methods through simulations. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, since particle filtering is often used in control systems and robotics, cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely sub-categories.
